The "'''geek lobby'''" is the set of influential actors from the [[high-tech industry]] which use their power and influence to sway government policy.<ref name="slate1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technocracy/2011/11/stop_online_piracy_act_can_the_geek_lobby_stop_hollywood_from_wrecking_the_internet_.html|title=The Rise of the Geek Lobby|last=Oremus|first=Will|date=2011-11-30|newspaper=Slate|language=en-US|issn=1091-2339|access-date=2017-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/arts-post/post/sopa-visual-petition-riles-up-the-geek-lobby/2011/12/13/gIQAD3PrrO_blog.html|title=SOPA visual petition riles up the ‘geek lobby’|last=Judkis|first=Maura|date=2011-12-13|website=Washington Post|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-24}}</ref> The geek lobby includes [[Google]], [[Facebook]], [[Apple Inc.]], [[Microsoft]], and others.

They often try to control or influence policies such as: [[online privacy]], [[net neutrality]], and others.<ref>http://iworkfortheinternet.org/</ref><ref name="slate1"/>

